content:
The `FileTree` component renders a hierarchical file and folder structure, commonly used in documentation explorers or file browsers.

## Key Exports

*   `FileTree`: The main React component for rendering the tree.

## Props

*   `nodes`: An array of `TreeNode` objects, where each node can be either a `FolderNode` or a `FileNode`. The `TreeNode` type is imported from `./lib/tree`.
*   `activeKey`: A string or null, representing the key of the currently selected file node.
*   `onSelect`: A callback function that is invoked when a file node is clicked. It receives the `key` of the selected file node.
*   `depth`: (Optional) A number representing the current nesting level of the tree, used for indentation. Defaults to 0.

## Internal Components

*   `FolderRow`: Renders a folder entry in the tree. It handles toggling the expansion/collapse state of its children.
*   `FileRow`: Renders a file entry in the tree. It highlights the row if it matches the `activeKey`.

## Usage Example

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { FileTree, TreeNode } from './FileTree'; // Assuming FileTree and TreeNode are exported from the same file or a library

// Sample tree data structure
const treeData: TreeNode[] = [
  {
    kind: 'folder',
    name: 'src',
    children: [
      {
        kind: 'folder',
        name: 'components',
        children: [
          { kind: 'file', name: 'Button.tsx', key: 'src/components/Button.tsx', title: 'Button Component' },
          { kind: 'file', name: 'Input.tsx', key: 'src/components/Input.tsx', title: 'Input Component' },
        ],
      },
      { kind: 'file', name: 'index.ts', key: 'src/index.ts', title: 'Main entry point' },
    ],
  },
  {
    kind: 'folder',
    name: 'lib',
    children: [
      { kind: 'file', name: 'tree.ts', key: 'lib/tree.ts', title: 'Tree node types' },
    ],
  },
  { kind: 'file', name: 'App.tsx', key: 'App.tsx', title: 'Main Application' },
];

function App() {
  const [activeFile, setActiveFile] = useState<string | null>('App.tsx');

  const handleSelectFile = (key: string) => {
    setActiveFile(key);
    // Logic to load or display the content of the selected file
    console.log('Selected file:', key);
  };

  return (
    <div className="file-tree-container">
      <h1>Project Files</h1>
      <FileTree
        nodes={treeData}
        activeKey={activeFile}
        onSelect={handleSelectFile}
      />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

This component assumes the existence of `TreeNode`, `FolderNode`, and `FileNode` types defined in `./lib/tree`, and corresponding CSS classes for styling (`tree-level`, `tree-folder-group`, `tree-row`, `tree-folder-row`, `tree-chevron`, `tree-icon`, `tree-name`, `tree-children`, `tree-file-row`, `active`).
